[SN]TITLE[SN]
Funeral for peacemaker Fr Gerry Reynolds of Clonard Monastery

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The funeral for the Redemptorist priest Father Gerry Reynolds, who worked for peace and reconciliation in Northern Ireland, has taken place.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Fr Reynolds was based for more than 30 years at Clonard Monastery in west Belfast, where the funeral was held.
Along with his friend Fr Alex Reid, Fr Reynolds was deeply committed to brokering peace.
Among the mourners were Deputy First Minister Martin McGuinness and Irish foreign minister Charlie Flanagan.
Ulster Unionist leader Mike Nesbitt and SDLP leader Colum Eastwood were also in attendance.
Fr Reynolds died on Monday at Belfast's Royal Victoria Hospital, following a short illness. He was 80.
